International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 7 Aug 2020
Source: OIE, WAHIS [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=35346


Lumpy skin disease [LSD], Russia
-----------------------------
Information received on 7 Aug 2020 from Dr Nikolay Vlasov, Deputy Head, Federal Service for Veterinary and Phytosanitary Surveillance , Ministry of Agriculture, Moscou, Russia
Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Aug 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 6 Aug 2020
Report date: 7 Aug 2020
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Aug 2020
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 23 Dec 2019
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Kujbyshevo, Uglovsky, Altayskiy Kray [Altay]
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Aug 2020
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 671 / 9 / 0 / - / -

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 1.34 / 0 / 0 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; quarantine; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; zoning; disinfection; disinfestation; process to inactivate the pathogenic agent in products or by-products; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Altajskaya veterinary laboratory (local laboratory) / cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 6 Aug 2020 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

["Between March and up to October 2019, 26 LSD outbreaks were reported in 6 Russian provinces, around 1/3 of the outbreaks reported in 2018. LSD outbreaks have been reported in 2019 to the east of previous outbreaks since 2015, along the border with Kazakhstan, across southern Siberia until Novosibirsk and Altai. LSD has been present in Russia since 2015.

Citation: EFSA (European Food Safety Authority), Calistri P, De Clercq K, Gubbins S, et al.: Scientific report on the lumpy skin disease epidemiological report IV: data collection and analysis. EFSA Journal. 2020; 18(2): 6010, 36; https://doi.org/10.2903/j.efsa.2020.6010.

A map of the reported LSD outbreaks in Russian Federation in 2016-2019 and the number of affected animals in each outbreak (source: OIE, Global Framework for the Progressive Control of Transboundary Diseases [GF-TADs]) can be seen at https://efsa.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.2903/j.efsa.2020.6010#efs26010-fig-0006. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Altayskiy kray [Altay], Russia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7656258,20563]
